        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:46PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 446 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Shawsville, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Shawsville...
Bent Mountain...
Mc Donalds Mill...
Elliston-Lafayette...
and Crockett Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
